{"SHACK":[{"def":"To shed or fall, as corn or grain at harvest.","pos":""},{"def":"To feed in stubble, or upon waste corn.","pos":""}],"SHACKLE":[{"def":"Something which confines the legs or arms so as to prevent their free motion; specifically, a ring or band inclosing the ankle or wrist, and fastened to a similar shackle on the other leg or arm, or to something else, by a chain or a strap; a gyve; a fetter.","pos":""},{"def":"Hence, that which checks or prevents free action.","pos":""}],"SHACKLOCK":[{"def":"A sort of shackle.","pos":""}]}